    "enneagramme.faq.title": "Frequently asked questions",
    "enneagramme.faq.subtitle": "Find answers to the most common questions",
    "enneagramme.faq.q1.question": "How is the Enneagram different from the MBTI®?",
    "enneagramme.faq.q1.answer": "The MBTI describes cognitive preferences; the Enneagram mainly describes deep motivations, core fears and defense mechanisms. They are complementary: one explains “how you function”, the other “why you function that way”.",
    "enneagramme.faq.q2.question": "Is it spiritual or psychological?",
    "enneagramme.faq.q2.answer": "Historically the Enneagram has spiritual roots; today it is used in personal development and coaching. It is not a clinical tool and its scientific basis is limited.",
    "enneagramme.faq.q3.question": "What are “wings” and “subtypes”?",
    "enneagramme.faq.q3.answer": "Wings are adjacent types that color your main type (e.g. 4w3, 4w5). Subtypes (instincts: self-preservation, social, sexual) modulate the expression of the type and explain strong variations within the same type.",
    "enneagramme.faq.q4.question": "Can you “change” type?",
    "enneagramme.faq.q4.answer": "The core type generally stays stable; what changes is your level of health/resources and how you handle your central fear. We speak of integration/disintegration rather than changing type.",
    "enneagramme.faq.q5.question": "Why do I see myself in several types?",
    "enneagramme.faq.q5.answer": "Behaviors overlap. The key is the core motivation and basic fear. Tests can help, but self-inquiry (concrete examples, reactions under stress, non-negotiable desires) is decisive.",
    "enneagramme.faq.q6.question": "How can I use the Enneagram without falling into labels?",
    "enneagramme.faq.q6.answer": "Use it like a map: a guide for language and understanding yourself/others, not a prison. Avoid quick judgments, favor curiosity, empathy and working on recurring patterns.",
    "enneagramme.faq.outro": "Have more questions? <a href=\"mailto:contact@personnalitecomparee.com\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-500 font-medium\">Contact us</a>",
