    "faq.subtitle": "Find answers to the most common questions",
    "faq.q1.question": "How does the weighting system work?",
    "faq.q1.answer": "Over time, we noticed that self-assessment often introduced bias.<br>The <strong>final result therefore relies solely on the evaluation of three relatives</strong> from your circle.<br><br>The system no longer <strong>takes the relationship into account</strong> (family, friend, colleague...) but analyzes the <strong>convergence of their answers</strong>.<br><br>➤ If their answers are <strong>highly consistent</strong>, the <strong>confidence score</strong> is high.<br>➤ If they are <strong>divergent</strong>, the score will be lower, helping you identify a profile that is still unclear or nuanced.<br><br>Your own self-assessment is always available, but only <strong>for information</strong> – it <strong>no longer influences the calculation</strong>.",
    "faq.q2.question": "Which artificial intelligence powers Psycho'Bot?",
    "faq.q2.answer": "Psycho'Bot runs on OpenAI's gpt-4o-mini model, a fast and affordable AI capable of providing precise, natural responses in real time.",
    "faq.q3.question": "Are my answers and those of my relatives anonymous?",
    "faq.q3.answer": "Yes. No identity is stored with the answers, and only the data needed to compute the profile is kept.",
    "faq.q4.question": "Is my access code valid for life?",
    "faq.q4.answer": "Yes. Your access code remains valid indefinitely, allowing you to view your results at any time with no time limit.",
    "faq.q5.question": "Can I see each relative's detailed answers?",
    "faq.q5.answer": "No. For confidentiality reasons, you cannot view the individual answers of your relatives. However, on your results page you can see the MBTI-inspired and Enneagram profile assigned to each relative based on their answers.",
    "faq.q6.question": "Can I get a personalized interpretation of my results?",
    "faq.q6.answer": "Yes. You can ask Psycho'Bot in the \"Chat with Psycho'Bot\" section for a personalized interpretation of your MBTI-inspired and Enneagram profile. Feel free to give it your profile and ask any questions you wish.",
